          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and bake the biscuits",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional. Line two baking trays with baking paper. Beat the butter and sugar together until light. Sift in the flour and cocoa and stir to a soft dough. Fold in the crushed cornflakes. Roll into balls of about 30 g each and place on the trays, pressing down gently to flatten slightly. Bake for 13 to 15 minutes until set. The biscuits will be soft when they come out; they firm as they cool. Leave on the trays for 5 minutes, then transfer to a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ice and decorate",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sift the icing sugar and cocoa together. Stir in the melted butter and enough hot water to make a thick, spreadable icing. Spread a generous teaspoon of icing on top of each cooled biscuit and press a walnut half into the centre. Allow to set.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
